Dynamic Visual Tracking: Features an auto-calculating ASCII progress bar (|#####---------------| 25%) that renders the completion ratio every time the interface refreshes.

Complete CRUD Functionality: Supports basic task operations including creating tasks, viewing current workflows with statuses ([PENDING] / [DONE]), updating completion status, and deleting entries from list memory.

State & Input Validation: Built-in exception handling safely filters empty string inputs and catches non-integer selections (ValueError), preventing the console application from crashing during unexpected user interactions.

Clean Object-Oriented Architecture: Entirely encapsulated inside a standalone ToDoListApp class structure, making it incredibly straightforward to refactor, expand, or integrate into a graphical user interface (GUI) later on.
